)attr default(%+_)
  _ type( input) intens(low ) just(left ) hilite(uscore) caps(on)
  ~ type(text) intens(high) caps(off) just(asis ) hilite(reverse) color(turq)
  [ type(output) intens(high) caps(off) just(left) pas(on) skip(on) color(white)
)Body Expand(\\)
%Tutorial -\-\~The z ISPF Git Interface (zigi)%\-\- Tutorial
%Selection ===>_ZCMD                                                          +
+
                              %Local Repositories+
+
%Row selections:
+
  %S+Select a repository to open and work with
+    - The repository will be opened with a list of managed z/OS datasets
+      and/or OMVS files.
  %I+Info on the repository
  %V+View the OMVS file system for the local repository
+    - Open the ISPF 3.17 (UDList) to allow viewing of the local repository
  %D+Delete the repository on the local file system
     - All OMVS files will be removed
+    - All z/OS datasets will NOT be deleted
+ %/+Display a popup for row selection options.
+
+    "Some things are so unexpected that no one is prepared for them."
+        - Leo Rosten
+
+Press the%Enter+key to continue your zigi tutorial journey.
)Init
 .cursor  = &zcmd
 &zcont = zigih110
)PROC
)END
